text:
1998年，我的『繞著力宏轉』演唱會在大安森林公園舉辦，20年後，我帶著這幾年與粉絲們約定好的新年禮物『福利秀』再次回到這裡。很期待能夠在新的一年的第一天跟大家一起度過的同時，有幾點也提醒大家
1. 演出是在1/1 18:00 開始。
2. 本場活動是免費無售票的，座位區我們提供給歌迷會的粉絲外，草皮區都是大家可以進入觀看演出。
3. 大安森林公園有很多美麗的花草，大家在觀看演出的同時記得愛護花圃區，不要踐踏。
4. 垃圾不落地，演出後也希望大家發揮愛心把垃圾帶走。
5. 周邊的停車位有限，鼓勵大家多多搭乘大眾交通工具前來。
6. 不攜帶任何爆裂物與違禁品，公園為無菸環境。
7. 不使用任何直播與相機進行錄音、錄影。

 我們2019.01.01 大安森林公園露天音樂台 不見不散！

如果你還沒有看到這個，等一下會很震驚！我們的世界變化越來越大！If you haven’t already seen this, get ready to be
blown away. Our world is changing! 
https://www.google.com/…/google-duplex-assistant-phone-call…

我朋友拍了一部關於象牙市場和大象即將面臨絕種的紀錄片。請支持香港禁止進口象牙。Hong Kong’s proposed ivory ban will allow
the city's ivory traders a further five years – in addition to the 27 they have
already had – to sell their ivory stocks. Yet the traders are still calling for
compensation. Meanwhile numerous “fresh” illegal shipments to Hong Kong have
been intercepted in recent years, the largest to date in July 2017 was over
seven tons. Giving ANY value to unsold stockpiles sends the wrong message and
would fuel the poaching of Africa's last remaining elephant populations. That's
why paying compensation to the traders is a bad idea. Please show your support
for the Hong Kong ivory ban – with NO COMPENSATION – ahead of the second Hong
Kong Legislative Council Public Hearing on the ivory ban scheduled for September
6, 2017.

#父親節快樂 ，願黃金時代最最精彩!!🏅️❤️ ​​​ Two years ago, on the day of his retirement, I
interviewed my dad in his office. He shared his thoughts and memories with me of
over half a century of medical practice. A precious 37 minute interview, that
forever captured that important moment. Dad, #HappyFathersDay and may your
Golden Years be the best ones yet!

Jinglei and we cried ourselves into two puddles of tears in the cinema! At
dinner, we recommended the film to Wangbaba and Wangmama, and they’re going to
see it tomorrow. I hope they bring lots of tissues...or maybe a mop!!! 😭
